Subject: wined3d: add Intel Battlemage G21

The GPU description table has no entry for device 0xe20b (Arc B580,
Battlemage G21), so wined3d reports the card through the generic Intel
fallback for feature level 11, "Intel(R) HD Graphics 4000". Ableton
Live 12 blacklists that description by name ("Unexplained slow UI at
zoom-level 100% and/or crashes"), refuses D3D11 and falls back to GDI,
even though the stack underneath is healthy (Mesa 26 identifies the
card as BMG G21). Add the real description so the reported adapter name
is truthful and no longer matches the blacklist.

Like the other post-HD4000 Intel entries the card reuses
DRIVER_INTEL_HD4000; this tree has no newer Intel driver class. VRAM is
12288 MiB (B580 12 GB).

Origin: local fix for issue #11 (Intel Arc B580 misidentified as HD
Graphics 4000). Should also be upstreamed to Wine.
---
 dlls/wined3d/directx.c         | 4 ++++
 dlls/wined3d/wined3d_private.h | 1 +
 2 files changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/wined3d/directx.c b/dlls/wined3d/directx.c
index 19ec807..3cc5e3f 100644
--- a/dlls/wined3d/directx.c
+++ b/dlls/wined3d/directx.c
@@ -666,6 +666,10 @@ static const struct wined3d_gpu_description gpu_description_table[] =
     {HW_VENDOR_INTEL,      CARD_INTEL_HD630_2,             "Intel(R) HD Graphics 630",                                  DRIVER_INTEL_HD4000,  3072},
     {HW_VENDOR_INTEL,      CARD_INTEL_UHD630_1,            "Intel(R) UHD Graphics 630",                                 DRIVER_INTEL_HD4000,  3072},
     {HW_VENDOR_INTEL,      CARD_INTEL_UHD630_2,            "Intel(R) UHD Graphics 630",                                 DRIVER_INTEL_HD4000,  3072},
+    /* Battlemage G21. Without this entry the card is reported through the
+     * generic Intel fallback ("Intel(R) HD Graphics 4000"), which Ableton
+     * Live 12 blacklists by name, disabling its GPU renderer. */
+    {HW_VENDOR_INTEL,      CARD_INTEL_BMG_G21,             "Intel(R) Arc(tm) B580 Graphics (BMG G21)",                  DRIVER_INTEL_HD4000,  12288},
 };
 
 static const struct driver_version_information *get_driver_version_info(enum wined3d_display_driver driver,
diff --git a/dlls/wined3d/wined3d_private.h b/dlls/wined3d/wined3d_private.h
index a145f59..82b4793 100644
--- a/dlls/wined3d/wined3d_private.h
+++ b/dlls/wined3d/wined3d_private.h
@@ -2451,6 +2451,7 @@ enum wined3d_pci_device
     CARD_INTEL_HD630_2              = 0x591b,
     CARD_INTEL_UHD630_1             = 0x3e9b,
     CARD_INTEL_UHD630_2             = 0x3e91,
+    CARD_INTEL_BMG_G21              = 0xe20b,
 };
 
 /* The driver names reflect the lowest GPU supported
